er=2&verse=22'>1Sa 2:22</a><br/> - Samuel's sons, taking bribes<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=8&verse=5'>1Sa 8:5</a> <br/> - Saul:<br/> b Sparing Agag and the best of the booty<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=15&verse=35'>1Sa 15:35</a><br/> b in jealousy plotting against David<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=18&verse=29'>1Sa 18:29</a><br/> b Seeking to slay David<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=19'>1Sa 19</a><br/> b Slaying Ahimelech and the priests<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=22&verse=19'>1Sa 22:19</a><br/> - Hanun, maltreating David's servants<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=10&verse=4'>2Sa 10:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=19&verse=5'>1Ch 19:5</a> <br/> - David, numbering Israel and Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=24&verse=9'>2Sa 24:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=21&verse=7'>1Ch 21:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=27&verse=24'>1Ch 27:24</a> <br/> - Solomon:<br/> b Luxurious and idolatrous<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=11&verse=13'>1Ki 11:13</a><br/> b Oppressing the people<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=12&verse=4'>1Ki 12:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=4&verse=23'>1Ki 4:23</a><br/> - Rehoboam, making the yoke heavy<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=12&verse=11'>1Ki 12:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=10&verse=15'>2Ch 10:15</a> <br/> - Jeroboam:<br/> b Perverting the true worship<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=12&verse=33'>1Ki 12:33</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=13&verse=5'>1Ki 13:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=14&verse=16'>1Ki 14:16</a><br/> b Exalting debased persons to the priesthood<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=12&verse=31'>1Ki 12:31</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=13&verse=33'>1Ki 13:33</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=32'>2Ki 17:32</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=11&verse=15'>2Ch 11:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=26&chapter=44&verse=7'>Eze 44:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=3&verse=10'>Num 3:10</a><br/> - Abijam, walking in the sins of Rehoboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=15&verse=3'>1Ki 15:3</a> <br/> - Nadab, walking in the ways of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=15&verse=26'>1Ki 15:26</a> <br/> - Baasha, walking in the ways of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=15&verse=34'>1Ki 15:34</a> <br/> - Asa, imprisoning the seer, and oppressing the people<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=16&verse=10'>2Ch 16:10</a> <br/> - Zimri, walking in the ways of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=19'>1Ki 16:19</a> <br/> - Omri, walking in the ways of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=29'>1Ki 16:29</a> <br/> - Ahab:<br/> b Serving Baal<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=16&verse=33'>1Ki 16:33</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=21&verse=26'>1Ki 21:26</a><br/> b Confiscating Naboth's vineyard<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=21'>1Ki 21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=8&verse=14'>1Sa 8:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=22&verse=38'>1Ki 22:38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=9&verse=26'>2Ki 9:26</a><br/> - Jehoram, cleaving to the sins of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=3&verse=3'>2Ki 3:3</a> <br/> - Hazael, committing rapine<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=8&verse=12'>2Ki 8:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=10&verse=32'>2Ki 10:32</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=12&verse=17'>2Ki 12:17</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=7'>2Ki 13:7</a> <br/> - Jehoram, walking in the ways of the kings of Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=8&verse=18'>2Ki 8:18</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=21&verse=13'>2Ch 21:13</a> <br/> - Jehu, departing not from the sins of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=10&verse=29'>2Ki 10:29</a> <br/> - Jehoahaz, in following the sins of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=2'>2Ki 13:2</a> <br/> Jehoash, in following the wicked example of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=11'>2Ki 13:11</a><br/> - Jeroboam II, not departing from the sins of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=14&verse=24'>2Ki 14:24</a> <br/> - Zachariah, Menahem, Pekahiah, and Pekah:<br/> b Following the sins of Jeroboam<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=9'>2Ki 15:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=18'>2Ki 15:18</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=24'>2Ki 15:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=28'>2Ki 15:28</a><br/> b Conspiring against and slaying Pekahiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=25'>2Ki 15:25</a><br/> - Hoshea:<br/> b Who conspired against Pekah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=30'>2Ki 15:30</a><br/> b in permitting Baal-worship<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=2'>2Ki 17:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=17&verse=18'>2Ki 17:18</a><br/> - Ahaz, burning his children in idolatrous sacrifice<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=16&verse=3'>2Ki 16:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=28&verse=4'>2Ch 28:4</a> <br/> - Manasseh, who committed the abominations of the heathen<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=21&verse=17'>2Ki 21:17</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=33&verse=7'>2Ch 33:7</a> <br/> - Amon, who followed the evil example of Manasseh<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=21&verse=22'>2Ki 21:22</a> <br/> - Jehoahaz, who followed in the ways of his fathers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=23&verse=32'>2Ki 23:32</a> <br/> - Jehoiakim, in walking in the ways of his fathers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=23&verse=37'>2Ki 23:37</a> <br/> - Jehoiachin, walking in the ways of his fathers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=24&verse=9'>2Ki 24:9</a> <br/> - Zedekiah:<br/> b Following the evil example of Jehoiakim<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=24&verse=19'>2Ki 24:19</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=36&verse=13'>2Ch 36:13</a><br/> b Persecuting Jeremiah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=38&verse=6'>Jer 38:6</a><br/> - Joash, slaying Zechariah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=24&verse=2'>2Ch 24:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=24&verse=25'>2Ch 24:25</a> <br/> - Ahaziah, doing evil after the house of Ahab<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=22&verse=9'>2Ch 22:9</a> <br/> - Amaziah, worshiping the gods of Seir<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=25&verse=14'>2Ch 25:14</a> <br/> - Uzziah, invading the priest's office<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=26&verse=16'>2Ch 26:16</a> <br/> - Ahasuerus and Haman, decreeing the death of the Jews<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=17&chapter=3&verse=15'>Est 3:15</a> <br/> - Nebuchadnezzar:<br/> b Commanding to destroy the wise men<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=2&verse=13'>Dan 2:13</a><br/> b Committing the three Hebrews to the furnace<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=3&verse=23'>Dan 3:23</a><br/> - Belshazzar, in drunkenness and committing sacrilege<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=5&verse=23'>Dan 5:23</a> <br/> - Darius, in deifying himself<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=6&verse=7'>Dan 6:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=6&verse=9'>Dan 6:9</a> <br/> - The princes, conspiring against Daniel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=27&chapter=6&verse=9'>Dan 6:9</a> <br/> - Herod the Great, slaying the children in Bethlehem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=2&verse=18'>Mat 2:18</a> <br/> - Herod Antipas:<br/> b in beheading John the Baptist<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=14&verse=11'>Mat 14:11</a><br/> b in craftiness and tyranny<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=13&verse=32'>Luk 13:32</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=23&verse=15'>Luk 23:15</a><br/> - Herod Agrippa, persecuting the church<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=12&verse=19'>Act 12:19</a> <br/> - Pilate, delivering Jesus for crucifixion<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=27&verse=26'>Mat 27:26